Chilean Stocks: Madeco and Sonda Advance; Lan Airlines Retreats

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-28T20:52:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/chilean-stocks-madeco-and-sonda-advance-lan-airlines-retreats.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:13 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 0.1 percent to 4,593.40. The MSCI Chile
Index fell 0.3 percent to 2,646.84.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   retreated for a second day,
falling 0.7 percent to 12,295 pesos. Latin America’s largest
airline by market value has lost 1.7 percent in the two trading
days since El Mercurio reported it would halt direct flights to
Toronto because of higher  oil prices  and after local rival Pal
Airlines lodged an antitrust complaint against the company.  Madeco SA (MADECO)   increased 4 percent to 26.77 pesos.
The Chilean copper products company agreed to increase its stake
in  France ’s Nexans SA to 20 percent from 9 percent.  Sonda SA (SONDA)   gained 4 percent to a six-week high of
1,195.6 pesos. The information technology company replaced
retailer Cencosud SA as Santiago-based broker IM Trust SA’s top
pick among Chilean stocks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  